==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moniliform
<hw>Mo*nil"i*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>monile</ets> necklace + <ets>-form</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>moniliforme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Joined or
constricted, at regular intervals, so as to resemble a string of beads;
<as>as, a <ex>moniliform</ex> root; a <ex>moniliform</ex> antenna</as>.
See <ex>Illust</ex>. of <er>Antenna</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moniment</ent>⟦br⟧
